en_218291_0	Prime Minister Ranil Wickremasinghe has said that it is the present Government that has spent a colossal sum on the development of the village.
en_218291_1	The Prime Minister also vested in the people the newly constructed Baddegama Divisional Secretariat with the intention of making the public service more efficient.
en_218291_2	The expenditure incurred on it was 87.4 million rupees.
en_218291_3	The building will house a fully-fledged auditorium with a seating capacity of 300 and also a vehicle park.
en_218291_4	The Prime Minister handed over Samurdhi entitlements to 1000 low income families within the Baddegama Divisional Secretariat Division.
en_218291_5	Addressing a function that followed the opening, Prime Minister Ranil Wickremasinghe mentioned that it is the present Government that has spent a highest amount for development that is taking place in the village.
